<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-153] lazystatfs option should be documented (Ch 32, Ch 16)</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-153</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If one or more OSTs are active yet unavailable, standard &apos;df&apos; will hang unless the lazystatfs option is specified.  &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Additionally, &amp;#39;lfs df&amp;#39; can be used instead.&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The option should be documented in the Ops Manual.  It should be noted that the reported information will be inaccurate (and that there is no way to tell from &apos;df&apos; that that is the case).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="19202">LUDOC-153</key>
