&lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7674/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/#/c/7674/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="61987" author="linda" created="Tue, 9 Jul 2013 23:40:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Comment from Lustre-discuss 19-0ct-2010&lt;br/&gt;
There is actually a mount option (namely lazystatfs, added in 1.8.0) which allows statfs to skip inactive OSTs. This feature can also be enabled on a live system with &quot;lctl set_param llite.*.lazystatfs=1&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
